value.name: Colesbukta – Wikipedia
value.snippet: Colesbukta er en 4,5 km bred bukt på sørsiden av Isfjorden, nordvest på Nordenskiöld Land på Spitsbergen, Svalbard. Colesbukta ligger omtrent midtveis mellom Adventfjorden og Grønfjorden. I Colesbukta er det rikt planteliv, blant annet med multe som ellers er svært uvanlig på Svalbard.

value.name: Colesbukta - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Colesbukta is a bay at the southern side of Isfjorden, in Nordenskiöld Land at Spitsbergen, Svalbard. The bay is about 4.5 kilometer wide. A railway for coal transport was earlier operated between Grumantbyen and shipment facilities in Colesbukta. The valley Colesdalen debouches into Colesbukta.

value.name: Colesbukta – Wikipedia
value.snippet: Colesbukta är en 4,5 kilometer bred bukt på södra sidan av Isfjorden på Nordenskiöld Land på Spetsbergen i Svalbard. Colesbukta ligger ungefär mitt emellan Adventfjorden (Longyearbyen) och Grønfjorden (Barentsburg). I Colesbukta är det ett rikt växtliv, med bland annat hjortron, som annars är sällsynta i Svalbard.

value.name: Panoramas Colesbukta - Spitsbergen | Svalbard
value.snippet: Coles­buk­ta was a small Rus­si­an sett­le­ment that was used until 1962 to ship coal that was mined in neigh­bou­ring Gru­mant­by­en. value.name: Colesbukta – Wikipedia
value.snippet: Colesbukta ist eine 4,5 km breite Bucht an der Südseite des Isfjord auf Spitzbergen. In die Bucht mündet der durch Colesdalen fließende Fluss Coleselva. Colesdalen gilt als eine der vegetationsreichsten Gegenden auf Spitzbergen.

value.name: Colesbukta | Oceanwide Expeditions
value.snippet: Colesbukta is a bay in southern Isfjorden, a fjord of Spitsbergen, the largest island in the Svalbard archipelago. Measuring 4.5 km (2.8 miles) wide, Colesbukta was the site of Russian coal facilities shipping to Grumant, another Soviet settlement. value.name: Grumant and Colesbukta the Soviet Ghost Towns - Young Pioneer Tours
value.snippet: Originally established in 1912 it eventually came under Soviet control, with mining going on until it was abandoned in 1965. It’s population peaked at 1,106 in 1951 making it the third most important Russian settlement in Svalbard, although that does make it last.

value.name: Colesbukta – Store norske leksikon
value.snippet: Colesbukta er en 4,5 km bred, åpen bukt på sørsiden av den ytre delen av Isfjorden, Spitsbergen, Svalbard, mellom Grumantbyen og Barentsburg. Det er registrert mange kulturminner i området, både fra gruvetiden og tidligere prospekterings- og fangstvirksomhet.

value.name: Barentsburg - Colesbukta - Spitsbergen | Svalbard
value.snippet: Sun 29 Mar 2015. The trip to Barents­burg takes about 3 hours. We make use of the fine wea­ther by doing a bit of pho­to shoo­ting. The times, they are a chan­gin’ … cle­ar­ly and visi­bly also here in Barents­burg, whe­re coal is still being mined, but the past has brought dif­fi­cul­ties and acci­dents in the mines and the future may be some­whe­re more sun­ny.
